About 200,000 machines have been infected worldwide by the ransomware &ldquo;WannaCry&rdquo;
An Indian-origin security researcher with Google has found evidence suggesting that North Korean hackers may have carried out the &ldquo;unprecedented&rdquo; ransomware cyberattack that hit over 150 countries, including India. Neel Mehta has published a code which a Russian security firm has termed as the &ldquo;most significant clue to date&rdquo;, BBC reported today.
The code, published on Twitter, is exclusive to North Korean hackers, researchers said.
